contentrichtext.text: '''UDT''' may refer to: * [[Underwater Demolition Team]], American commando team and the precursor to the U.S. Navy SEALs * [[Chadian Democratic Union]] (Union Démocratique Tchadienne), the second African political party ever created in Chad * [[Timorese Democratic Union]] (União Democrática Timorense), a conservative political party in East Timor * [[UDP-based Data Transfer Protocol]], a high performance data transport protocol and its open source library * [[Uitgeverij De Tijd]], a former Belgian publisher * Unarmed Defensive Tactics, as employed by various [[Police]] Forces as part of their training * [[Cryptorchidism|Undescended testes]], a developmental abnormality in which the testes do not properly descend into the scrotum * [[Union of Djibouti Workers]], a trade union centre in Djibouti * [[Universal Diver Training]], a [[Scuba diving|SCUBA]] diver training organization * [[User-defined tag]], a concept in [[Financial Information eXchange]] protocol to help customize messaging between various parties * [[User-defined type]], a concept in computer science that is generally synonymous with "record", "structure", "composite type" or "class" * [[Yonkers UDT]], a sport scuba diving club in [[Yonkers]], New York, USA {{disambig}}
